James DARIENZO, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 465. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 22, 1936. Maxwell Shapiro, of New York City (Asa S. Herzog, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. - ■ Lamar Hardy, U. S., Atty., of New York City (John J. Dowling, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Paul Nulle, Special Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N~ HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
